h3. Issue Summary

Configuring an external gadget using a local gadget URL breaks the new gadget
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Navigate to a dashboard you can edit;
 # Select *Add gadget* and click to load all gadgets;
 # Select any *Local* gadgets and click to "Show XML link" to any of them;
 # Copy the XML Link;
 # Click to *Manage gadgets*;
 # Include the XML Link (from the same instance);
 # Navigate back to the dashboard and add the external version of the gadget we created;

h3. Expected Results

The gadget works as if it was a local one;
h3. Actual Results
 * Fields are not editable;
 * Reording fields do not work;
 * Adding fields work but removing doesn't

h3. Workaround

Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary

The underscore is a valid and unreserved character as per the [RFC 3986|http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc3986], section 2.3, but Jira shows an error instead.

!image-2020-06-19-16-18-16-910.png|width=525,height=242!

Ideally, Jira should accept any valid characters.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Navigate to an issue;
 # Click More > Link;
 # Select Web Link;
 # Enter a URL containing an underscore and any Link Text;
 # Click Create.

h3. Expected Results

The URL should be linked successfully.
h3. Actual Results

The error message is shown:

 
{noformat}
Invalid 'URL'. Make sure tou include the full URL (e.g. http://www.google.com).{noformat}
h3. Workaround

Utilize the IP address instead, or add a DNS entry utilizing only alphanumeric and hyphens.

h3. Issue Summary

The help text on the "Add SMTP Mail Server" page is confusing for some users. The help text suggests port 465 for SMTPS, while the majority of mail providers at this time are using 587 with STARTTLS for outgoing mail. Port 465 should not be used in most contexts - reference: [https://www.mailgun.com/blog/which-smtp-port-understanding-ports-25-465-587/]
h3. Quick fix

Change the *SMTP Port* help text _from_
{code:java}
Optional - SMTP port number to use. Leave blank for default (defaults: SMTP - 25, SMTPS - 465).{code}
to
{code:java}
Optional - SMTP port number to use. Enter 587 and select the TLS checkbox below for STARTTLS. Leave blank for default (defaults: SMTP - 25, SMTPS - 465).{code}
h3. Longer fix

Change the layout of the page to suggest STARTTLS as the secure option to use instead of SMTPS. Potentially add this as an option in the Protocol dropdown (which would remove the TLS checkbox)
